when you add signal handlers for SIGUSR1,SIGUSR2 to send DTR/RTS, in time-write.ch add
  volatile
before
  int fd = -1, fd2 = -1;
and in time-write.ch in signal handler for SIGUSR1 use
  int dtr = TIOCM_DTR;
  if (serial_port_opened()) ioctl(fd, TIOCMSET, &dtr), ioctl(fd2, TIOCMSET, &dtr);
and in time-write.ch in signal handler for SIGUSR2 use
  int rts = TIOCM_RTS;
  if (serial_port_opened()) ioctl(fd, TIOCMSET, &rts), ioctl(fd2, TIOCMSET, &rts);
(in time-write.w omit fd2 part)

========= If it will be necessary to fill buffer with two stripes ==========

in seconds.ch change
  @<Initialize display@>@;
into
  @<Initialize display@>=

create detect.ch
@x
@<Initialize display@>@;
@y
<Fill buffer: top and botom rows with 1, the rest with 0>
@<Initialize display@>@;
@<Display buffer@>@;
@z
